14:16.238 --> 14:17.672
♪ Well, I'm the bad boy ♪

14:17.740 --> 14:20.107
♪ Who looks like
he might carry a knife ♪

14:20.209 --> 14:22.542
♪ And I'll be in 'n' out of rehab ♪

14:22.611 --> 14:24.611
♪ For the rest of my life ♪

14:24.713 --> 14:26.780
♪ And there's this random old dude ♪

14:26.849 --> 14:28.949
♪ Who looks out of place ♪

14:29.051 --> 14:30.818
♪ And he always says... ♪

14:30.886 --> 14:33.420
I'm not in the band!
Get that camera out of my face!

14:33.488 --> 14:36.688
♪ Street II Men is dancing
on your street tonight ♪

14:36.746 --> 14:37.758
♪ Whoa, oh, oh ♪

14:37.844 --> 14:40.794
♪ Men II Street is singing
in your dreams tonight ♪

14:40.863 --> 14:41.774
♪ Whoa, oh, oh ♪

14:41.831 --> 14:43.530
♪ Men II Street, on your feet ♪

14:43.632 --> 14:46.366
♪ Feel the heat tonight ♪

14:46.468 --> 14:48.735
That's right, mean ol' Mrs. H

14:48.804 --> 14:50.762
is fully responsible for this video.

14:52.106 --> 14:54.129
Hey, why are you all laughing?

14:54.176 --> 14:56.943
It's like they took the worst
parts of every boy band song

14:57.011 --> 14:58.083
and mashed them together.

14:58.169 --> 15:00.613
Why were you wearing ski pants
on a spaceship?

15:00.716 --> 15:02.782
'Cause our love's icy hot
and outta this world.

15:02.884 --> 15:04.050
How's that not clear?

15:04.152 --> 15:06.653
Okay, but why were you all
hanging around in T-shirts

15:06.755 --> 15:07.887
on one bed?

15:07.989 --> 15:09.361
Why were we on that bed?

15:11.493 --> 15:14.894
Oh, my God, this song is awful
and my dreams are shallow.

15:14.996 --> 15:18.598
Your faculty advisor/dreammaker
will fix this!

15:18.700 --> 15:19.666
Don't.

15:19.768 --> 15:21.334
You've done enough already.

15:21.436 --> 15:22.836
I guess you were right.

15:22.937 --> 15:25.572
My big, angry attempt
to show them nice Wilma

15:25.674 --> 15:26.906
only made it worse.

15:27.008 --> 15:29.541
Look, I know you're hurt
by how the kids see you...

15:29.643 --> 15:31.643
To be clear...

15:31.746 --> 15:33.145
I'm very hurt.

15:33.248 --> 15:35.014
But I'll always be me, so it's best

15:35.116 --> 15:36.548
if I just get used to it.

15:39.811 --> 15:43.270
<i>In just one week, Julie's stint
as school nurse was done.</i>

15:43.333 --> 15:45.586
Well, I guess that's it.

15:45.649 --> 15:47.916
Thanks again for giving me
this opportunity.

15:47.970 --> 15:51.638
- Not so fast.
- Oh, God, he's back to fight more.

15:51.708 --> 15:53.307
I'm here to fix this.

15:53.375 --> 15:55.810
You see, I realized there is
a way to make this work.

15:55.870 --> 15:57.845
I'm gonna get rid of all my quirks.

15:57.914 --> 16:00.181
Julie wants me to wear pants...

16:00.249 --> 16:01.816
then I'll wear pants.

16:01.884 --> 16:02.883
For love.

16:02.952 --> 16:04.018
I don't know what's happening,

16:04.087 --> 16:05.264
but I'm certain that's not a thing.

16:06.488 --> 16:07.588
This is unsettling.

16:07.656 --> 16:09.122
I'm just new to the process.

16:09.191 --> 16:11.390
Well, you're doing it wrong, man!
Do it right!

16:11.459 --> 16:12.558
- If I stand my...
- What is this?

16:12.627 --> 16:13.860
Just bend your knees
like a normal human person.

16:13.962 --> 16:16.196
- My legs will adjust.
- It's hard to watch.

16:16.297 --> 16:18.164
Just walk normal, please!

16:18.233 --> 16:20.033
Stop yelling at me, I'm doing my best!

16:20.102 --> 16:22.168
I didn't ask you to change!
Not like this!

16:22.270 --> 16:24.604
See? Mellor wears shorts,
Wilma is scary.

16:24.672 --> 16:25.705
We are who we are!

16:25.774 --> 16:26.940
It doesn't mean you can give up.

16:27.008 --> 16:28.110
There's a way to be Wilma

16:28.157 --> 16:30.188
- and support these kids in your own way.
- Ah, man.

16:30.235 --> 16:32.078
Ah, somebody please help me!

16:32.147 --> 16:34.214
Maybe you're right,
maybe all that matters

16:34.315 --> 16:35.715
is I'm there for the kids...

16:35.784 --> 16:37.350
even if they find it mean and scary.

16:37.418 --> 16:38.885
Well, just do one leg at a time!

16:38.954 --> 16:40.153
You're jamming it up down there!

16:40.222 --> 16:42.188
Rick, if you take a seat,
you can do the left foot...

16:45.626 --> 16:47.059
All right, Street II Men.

16:47.128 --> 16:48.627
Enough pouting, time to fix this.

16:48.695 --> 16:51.263
Fix it? You made us a laughing
stock to the whole school!

16:51.331 --> 16:52.464
I did do that, yes.

16:52.532 --> 16:54.032
I was just trying to be supportive.

16:54.101 --> 16:56.735
Sure, maybe it seems
it's tough and scary,

16:56.804 --> 16:58.036
but that's just me.

16:58.105 --> 16:59.805
And unlike all your other teachers,

16:59.874 --> 17:01.206
when you got Wilma on your side,

17:01.275 --> 17:04.608
you got the cold, hard truth
and red-hot results.

17:04.678 --> 17:07.246
Only result was school-wide mockery.

17:07.314 --> 17:09.481
So your first music video
was a disaster.

17:09.549 --> 17:12.885
Still showed that you guys got
killer moves and voices.

17:12.953 --> 17:15.453
So get off your asses and go
show everyone what you got.

17:15.521 --> 17:16.588
Street II Men has broken up.

17:16.656 --> 17:18.556
For now. But as we all know,

17:18.625 --> 17:22.026
every great boy band stages
an epic comeback reunion tour.

17:22.127 --> 17:23.127
Says who?

17:23.229 --> 17:24.663
Says the awkward, old guy in the group.

17:24.731 --> 17:25.896
You're not even in the band.

17:25.964 --> 17:27.231
We all know I'm in the band.

17:27.300 --> 17:28.266
Forget it, dude.

17:28.335 --> 17:30.435
That song got us
laughed out of the room.

17:30.504 --> 17:33.772
Then I say our boy band does
a song that no one can resist.

17:39.145 --> 17:43.658
♪ Although loneliness has always
been a friend of mine ♪

17:43.713 --> 17:44.649
Dude, stop!

17:44.751 --> 17:47.552
♪ I'm leavin' my life in your hands ♪

17:47.654 --> 17:48.853
You're making it worse for us.

17:48.955 --> 17:53.595
♪ People say I'm crazy
and that I am blind ♪

17:53.620 --> 17:54.535
Please don't.

17:54.560 --> 17:57.428
♪ Risking it all in a glance ♪

17:57.530 --> 17:58.995
Really should help him out.

17:59.097 --> 18:03.534
♪ And how you got me blind
is still a mystery ♪

18:03.636 --> 18:07.404
♪ I can't get you out of my head ♪

18:09.174 --> 18:13.577
♪ Don't care what is written
in your history ♪

18:13.679 --> 18:16.872
♪ As long as you're here with me ♪

18:17.282 --> 18:20.584
♪ I don't care who you are ♪

18:20.686 --> 18:22.819
♪ Where you're from ♪

18:22.920 --> 18:25.388
♪ What you did ♪

18:25.490 --> 18:28.358
♪ As long as you love me ♪

18:28.460 --> 18:30.526
♪ Who you are ♪

18:30.628 --> 18:32.595
♪ Where you're from ♪

18:32.697 --> 18:35.197
♪ What you did ♪

18:35.299 --> 18:38.501
♪ As long as you love me ♪

18:38.603 --> 18:40.269
<i>And so CB and Wilma</i>

18:40.372 --> 18:42.538
<i>inspired a comeback tour for the ages.</i>

18:42.640 --> 18:43.840
<i>Even though we all debated</i>

18:43.941 --> 18:45.775
<i>who was the greatest boy band
of the '90s,</i>

18:45.877 --> 18:48.378
<i>that day, everyone agreed
for one fleeting moment</i>

18:48.480 --> 18:49.846
<i>it was Street II Men.</i>

18:49.947 --> 18:51.914
Julie, wait.

18:54.551 --> 18:56.017
Don't quit this job.

18:56.119 --> 18:57.853
This school could use a nurse like you.

18:57.954 --> 18:59.654
What about us?

18:59.757 --> 19:01.623
We went from not having one fight

19:01.725 --> 19:03.124
to having every one possible.

19:03.226 --> 19:04.225
Exactly!

19:04.327 --> 19:06.127
Does it bother me that you can't park

19:06.229 --> 19:07.929
or that you obsess over the dishwasher

19:08.031 --> 19:10.098
or that you hate ketchup
but love tomatoes?

19:10.200 --> 19:11.833
Yes, it's insane.

19:11.935 --> 19:14.168
The point is,
if those are your worst flaws,

19:14.271 --> 19:15.837
then I'll take them.

19:15.939 --> 19:17.071
I'll take all of it

19:17.140 --> 19:19.608
because your quirks are
what make you my Julie,

19:19.710 --> 19:21.443
and I wouldn't have it any other way.

19:21.512 --> 19:23.578
Then I'll keep being my quirky self.

19:25.215 --> 19:26.515
And you keep wearing shorts.

19:26.617 --> 19:30.652
- ♪ I don't care who you are ♪
- ♪ Who you are ♪

19:30.754 --> 19:31.872
♪ Where you're from ♪

19:31.942 --> 19:33.120
<i>No one's perfect.</i>

19:33.188 --> 19:35.355
<i>We all have crazy quirks
and impossible dreams,</i>

19:35.425 --> 19:37.858
<i>and we're often seen in ways
that we wish weren't true.</i>

19:37.960 --> 19:40.861
<i>But the thing is, it's a whole
lot easier to accept yourself</i>

19:40.930 --> 19:44.298
<i>when you're surrounded
by people who believe in you.</i>

19:44.366 --> 19:45.433
Hey, Mrs. H.

19:45.535 --> 19:47.501
Could really use some help
from my faculty advisor.

19:47.603 --> 19:50.070
You know, trying to figure out
where to go after high school.

19:50.139 --> 19:51.405
I thought it was top of the charts.

19:51.474 --> 19:54.542
Well, actually,
after your scary pep talk,

19:54.610 --> 19:57.144
I was thinking maybe less boy band

19:57.246 --> 20:00.213
and more music college.

20:00.316 --> 20:01.482
Now we're talking.

20:01.551 --> 20:03.916
♪ As long as you love me ♪

20:03.970 --> 20:05.652
<i>Truth is, at the end of the day,</i>

20:05.754 --> 20:09.564
<i>all of your flaws
are what make you perfect.</i>

20:09.627 --> 20:11.124
♪ As long as you love me ♪

